Advanced Version (Blink Pattern)

Sometimes a blink pattern is easier to see.

#!/bin/bash

TARGET="192.168.1.1"
PORT="445"
TIMEOUT=2

LED SETUP
LED ATTACK

nc -z -w $TIMEOUT $TARGET $PORT

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    while true
    do
        LED GREEN
        sleep 0.5
        LED OFF
        sleep 0.5
    done
else
    while true
    do
        LED RED
        sleep 0.5
        LED OFF
        sleep 0.5
    done
fi
Multi-Port Version (More Powerful)

This scans several ports and logs them.

#!/bin/bash

TARGET="192.168.1.1"
PORTS="22 80 443 445"

LED SETUP
LED ATTACK

for PORT in $PORTS
do
    nc -z -w 2 $TARGET $PORT

    if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
        LED GREEN
        sleep 1
    else
        LED RED
        sleep 1
    fi
done

LED OFF
